cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with text processing and representation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of intelligent computing and memory infrastructure, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of wordnet for semantic memory indicates that it could be classified under cs.LG (Learning). The paper also discusses the reduction of redundancy and storage of temporal relations, which could be related to information retrieval (IR) and neural networks (NE), respectively. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories.
